{"_id":"DTz1gyIdoEVpCvZo","data":{"ab":1,"ammo":{"burst":false,"longReload":false,"max":6,"suppress":false,"type":"typeAPower","value":6},"cost":1250,"damage":"2d12","description":"Distortion cannons are among the most sophisticated man-portable weapons designed before the Scream. These two-handed energy weapons rely on the same principle as does a spike drive, manipulating the underlying fabric of space to disrupt a target. Provided the wielder can see a target within range or accurately fix its location within one meter, the distortion cannon can ignore up to one meter of solid cover between the gun and its target","encumbrance":2,"location":"other","quality":"stock","range":{"max":300,"normal":100},"shock":{"ac":15,"dmg":0},"skill":"","stat":"dex","tl":5},"name":"Distortion Cannon","type":"weapon"}
{"_id":"GQfiji0YsuTXtx8J","data":{"ab":0,"ammo":{"burst":false,"longReload":false,"max":0,"suppress":false,"type":"special","value":0},"cost":25,"damage":"2d6","description":"Grenade users always roll to attack AC 10. On a miss, the grenade lands 1d10 meters away from the target in a random direction. Hit or miss, the grenade then explodes for 2d6 damage to all targets within 5 meters. Victims are allowed an Evasion save for half damage. Targets take 1 less point of damage for each point of AC above 14. Grenades can be thrown with the Exert skill instead of Shoot, if desired.","encumbrance":1,"location":"other","quality":"stock","range":{"max":30,"normal":10},"shock":{"ac":15,"dmg":0},"skill":"","stat":"dex","tl":3},"name":"Grenade","type":"weapon"}
